Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (South Ionian) pottery cup; very micaceous clay; interior glazed with added red band lined in white; reserved on the outside except for a band on upper wall; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.858)
